 Guns N' Roses 的 Duff McKagan 并不介意人工智能艺术：“我的皮肤总是看起来棒极了” https://www.nme.com/news/music/guns-n-roses-duff-mckagan-doesnt-mind-ai-art-my-skin-always-looks-amazing-in-it-3777519?utm_source= rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=枪炮玫瑰达夫麦卡根不介意人工智能艺术我的皮肤总是看起来很神奇Liberty DunworthWed, 24 Jul 2024 13:06:02 +0000 Music NewsNewsAIRock https://www.nme.com/?p=3777519 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="达夫·麦卡根 (Duff McKagan) 将于 2023 年现场表演" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>他也不认为这项技术会对音乐家构成真正的威胁</p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/guns-n-roses-duff-mckagan-doesnt-mind-ai-art-my-skin-always-looks-amazing-in-it-3777519">Guns N&#39; Roses 乐队的 Duff McKagan 并不介意 AI 艺术：“我的皮肤穿上它总是看起来棒极了”，</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="达夫·麦卡根 (Duff McKagan) 将于 2023 年现场表演" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/guns-n-roses">枪与玫瑰乐团的达夫·</a><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/duff-mckagan">麦卡根 (Duff McKagan</a> ) 表示，他很乐意在艺术作品中使用人工智能 (AI)。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多：<a href="https://www.nme.com/features/how-ai-is-pushing-the-boundaries-of-entertainment-3409263"><b>超越人类想象：人工智能如何突破娱乐界限</b></a></strong></li></ul><p>这位贝斯手在接受<a href="https://www.loudersound.com/news/bruce-springsteen-born-in-the-usa-classic-rock-330" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>《经典摇滚杂志》</em></a>的新采访时讨论了人工智能在创意领域的应用这个有争议的话题，并解释说他并不像一些艺术家那样反对这个概念。</p><p>在谈话中，这位音乐家被问及他是否认为技术的快速进步可能会对摇滚音乐的未来构成威胁，他回答说，他不太担心这会损害真正的艺术家。</p><p> “就音乐而言，对于枪炮玫瑰这样的摇滚乐队来说，它并不适用。我认为不可能，”他说。 “没有什么比坐下来用原声吉他写歌更好的了。永远不会有比这更好的事情了。”</p><p>他继续解释说，他对这项技术并不那么敌视，因为他看到粉丝们使用它来创作受 GNR 启发的艺术品，然后将其发送给他。</p><p> “我在 Instagram 上看到了 Guns N&#39; Roses 的 Al 艺术作品，其中一些东西很棒，而且我的皮肤总是看起来很棒。我想：‘我喜欢这个阿尔，我的头发！那件外套！我希望我有那件外套！</p><p> “但说实话，我对此了解得还不够……至于它适用于音乐，我根本看不到它。” </p><figure id="attachment_3777527" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3777527" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3777527" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan-live@2000x1270.jpg" alt="枪与玫瑰乐队创始成员达夫·麦卡根 (Duff McKagan) 登台表演" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan-live@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan-live@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan-live@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan-live@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan-live@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKagan-live@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3777527" class="wp-caption-text">枪与玫瑰乐队的创始成员达夫·麦卡根 (Duff McKagan) 在舞台上表演。图片来源：斯科特·杜德尔森/盖蒂图片社</figcaption></figure><p>这些评论呼应了<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/duff-mckagan-not-worried-about-ai-in-music-its-not-gonna-affect-my-creativity-3511911">麦卡根去年与<em>NME</em>分享的类似声明，当时他表示他不打算让人工智能“影响我的创造力”</a> 。</p><p> “总会有像我这样的人竖起中指。他们只会继续创作，甚至不会去关注它，真的，”他在直播中宣传他的单曲《灯塔》时说道。</p><p> “我不注意它。我并不担心。这不会影响我的创造力。”</p><p>他与越来越多的艺术家一起公开反对使用人工智能，其中包括<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/queens-brian-may-says-use-of-ai-in-music-is-massively-scary-3496017">布莱恩·梅 (Brian May)</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/ed-sheeran-expresses-his-fears-over-weird-ai-technology-3479746">艾德·希兰 (Ed Sheeran)</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/john-lydon-says-ai-will-ultimately-make-decisions-for-you-and-thats-very-dangerous-3475228">约翰·莱登 (John Lydon)</a> 。</p><p>然而，最多产的艺术家发声实例之一来自<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/nick-cave-and-the-bad-seeds">Bad Seeds</a>主唱<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/nick-cave">尼克·凯夫 (Nick Cave)</a> ，他<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nick-cave-calls-chatgpt-and-ai-songwriting-a-grotesque-mockery-of-what-it-is-to-be-human-3381620">将这一概念描述为“对人类本质的怪诞嘲讽”</a> 。他后来补充说<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nick-cave-chatgpt-should-just-fuck-off-and-leave-songwriting-alone-3421859">，他希望像 ChatGPT 这样的人工智能平台“滚蛋，别管歌曲创作了”</a> 。</p><p>同样，Guns N&#39; Roses 乐队成员<a href="/artists/slash">Slash</a>也参与了这场争论，并表示<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/slash-says-that-use-of-ai-in-music-does-not-really-thrill-me-3759692">在音乐中使用人工智能“并没有真正令我兴奋”</a> 。</p><p>虽然<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-reckons-the-use-of-ai-in-music-will-probably-shape-all-minds-going-forward-for-the-rest-of-time-3611901">像 Grimes 这样的艺术家已经接受了人工智能被用来帮助歌曲创作的想法</a>，但无数的名字却采取了不同的立场。例如，包括<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/billie-eilish">Billie Eilish</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/robert-smith">Robert Smith</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/stevie-wonder">Stevie Wonder</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/nicki-minaj">Nicki Minaj</a>在内的 200 多名艺术家最近<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/billie-eilish-robert-smith-more-sign-open-letter-against-predatory-use-of-ai-in-music-3612507">签署了一封由艺术家权利联盟编写的公开信</a>，警告不要在音乐中“掠夺性”使用人工智能。 </p><figure id="attachment_3777528" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3777528" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3777528" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKaganperforms@2000x1270.jpg" alt="枪与玫瑰乐团的达夫·麦卡根 (Duff McKagan) 于 2023 年 6 月 5 日在以色列特拉维夫的哈亚康公园演出。" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKaganperforms@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKaganperforms@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKaganperforms@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKaganperforms@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKaganperforms@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Duff-McKaganperforms@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3777528" class="wp-caption-text">枪花乐队 (Guns N&#39; Roses) 的达夫·麦卡根 (Duff McKagan) 将于 2023 年演出（摄影：Shlomi Pinto/Redferns）</figcaption></figure><p>在其他地方，国会议员建议<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/mps-suggest-musicians-and-celebrities-should-be-protected-against-ai-deepfakes-3752320">应该通过法律保护音乐家和名人免受人工智能深度假货的侵害</a>， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sony-music-umg-and-warner-records-sue-ai-brands-for-copyright-violations-3768405">索尼音乐、UMG 和华纳唱片公司都起诉了</a>两个人工智能品牌侵犯版权。后者的消息发布前不久<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sony-music-hit-out-at-tech-giants-and-demand-answers-for-unauthorised-a-i-songs-3759846">，索尼音乐就未经授权的人工智能歌曲对谷歌、微软、OpenAI 和其他科技公司进行了猛烈抨击</a>。</p><p>这也引发了电影行业的强烈反对，因为近年来演员越来越多地参与人工智能（无论是自愿还是不自愿）。</p><p>最近， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/scarlett-johansson-addresses-clash-with-open-ai-highlights-how-vulnerable-everybody-is-3768569">斯嘉丽约翰逊公开表达了她与人工智能公司 OpenAI 的分歧，</a>据称他们在新的 ChatGPT 系统中使用了与她相似的声音。</p><p>早在五月份， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/scarlett-johansson-claims-openai-used-a-voice-similar-to-hers-for-chatgpt-even-after-she-denied-their-offer-to-collaborate-3758115">这位演员就声称，当她听到系统的新语音选项</a>“Sky”时，她和她的朋友和家人注意到他们的声音很相似。结果她向OpenAI投诉，语音选项被删除了。</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/guns-n-roses-duff-mckagan-doesnt-mind-ai-art-my-skin-always-looks-amazing-in-it-3777519">Guns N&#39; Roses 乐队的 Duff McKagan 并不介意 AI 艺术：“我的皮肤穿上它总是看起来棒极了”，</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
尽管存在争议，Spotify 仍实现创纪录的季度利润，优质订阅用户数量增至 2.46 亿https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-record-quarterly-profits-246million-premium-subscribers-despite-controversies-3777495?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=spotify-record-quarterly-profits-246million-尽管有争议，但优质订阅者Liberty DunworthWed, 24 Jul 2024 12:22:21 +0000 Music NewsNewsSpotify https://www.nme.com/?p=3777495 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="一名男子走过显示 Spotify 徽标的屏幕" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>这些数字是在该流媒体服务推出价格上涨、裁员以及取消流媒体数量不足 1,000 首的歌曲之后发布的。</p><p>尽管争议首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-record-quarterly-profits-246million-premium-subscribers-despite-controversies-3777495">但 Spotify 创纪录的季度利润使优质订阅用户增至 2.46 亿</a>。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="一名男子走过显示 Spotify 徽标的屏幕" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/spotify">Spotify</a>透露，尽管围绕该平台存在争议，但本季度的利润和优质用户数量都超出了预期。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/artists-music-2023-challenges-2024-hopes-streaming-gigs-payment-blur-easy-life-cherise-lvra-get-cape-fac-3565687">艺术家谈 2023 年的挑战和 2024 年的希望：“我只想看到我们通过销售唱片获得报酬”</a></strong></li></ul><p>昨天（7 月 23 日）公布了 2024 年<a href="https://newsroom.spotify.com/2024-07-23/spotify-reports-second-quarter-2024-earnings/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">第二季度的数据</a>，这家流媒体巨头实现了创纪录的利润，超出了预期，付费订阅用户数量增加了 700 万。</p><p> Spotify 在报告中透露，其第二季度收入为 38.1 亿欧元（合 3.2 亿英镑），自上季度以来增长了 20%，净利润为 2.74 亿欧元（合 2.3 亿英镑），而净利润为 2.74 亿欧元（合 2.3 亿英镑）。前一年为 3.02 亿（2.53 亿英镑）。</p><p>它还表示，运营成本下降了16%，该期间的毛利率超出预期，为29.2%，而2023年为24.1%。</p><p>截至第二季度末，Spotify 月活跃用户数为 6.26 亿，增加了 1100 万，其中 Premium 订阅用户为 2.46 亿，增加了 700 万。在其他方面，该季度广告支持的收入增长了 13%，自数据披露以来，该平台的份额增长了 12% 以上。</p><p>虽然 Spotify 告诉股东，数字的飙升源于“健康的用户增长、货币化的改善和创纪录的盈利能力”，但还应该指出的是，利润也受到了该品牌最近做出的更具争议性决定的影响。 </p><figure id="attachment_3777505" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3777505" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3777505" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify-logo@2000x1270.jpg" alt="2024 年 6 月 19 日瑞典斯德哥尔摩 Spotify 公司总部全景。" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify-logo@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify-logo@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify-logo@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify-logo@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify-logo@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify-logo@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3777505" class="wp-caption-text"> 2024 年 6 月 19 日瑞典斯德哥尔摩 Spotify 公司总部全景。 （摄影：AaronP/Bauer-Griffin/GC Images）</figcaption></figure><p>其中包括流媒体服务<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-announce-new-premium-price-hike-for-the-us-3762105">在 6 月初提高了大部分现有计划的价格</a>——Spotify 在最近的声明中对此表示了认可。个人计划增加了 1 美元，从每月 10.99 美元增加到 11.99 美元（在英国为每月 10.99 英镑，原为 9.99 英镑），而家庭计划增加了 3 美元，从每月 16.99 美元增加到 19.99 美元。</p><p>同样， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-announces-cut-of-1500-jobs-with-17-per-cent-of-workforce-facing-axe-3552871">Spotify 决定在 2023 年底裁减 17% 的员工以节省成本，这也</a>将有助于利润的增长。这一决定是在之前实施的一项计划之后做出<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-to-cut-six-per-cent-of-workforce-3385265">的，该计划旨在于 2023 年初再裁员 6%，</a>以提高“速度”。</p><p>除了涨价和裁员之外，利润很可能还受益于流媒体服务<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-has-now-officially-demonetised-all-songs-with-less-than-1000-streams-3614010">正式取消平台上所有流媒体量不足 1000 首的歌曲</a>。</p><p>该政策于4月1日推出，但<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-confirm-songs-now-need-at-least-1000-streams-to-earn-royalties-3546548">平台已经筹划了一段时间</a>。它很快就受到批评，因为<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-announce-profit-and-millions-more-subscribers-but-also-royalty-cuts-to-less-popular-tracks-3521362">它让艺术家更难从他们的音乐中获得版税</a>，并限制了想要闯入音乐行业的新艺术家。</p><p>将播放量低于 1,000 首的歌曲取消货币化的决定并不是 Spotify 唯一一次因阻碍新艺术家从他们的作品中赚钱而面临艺术家和粉丝的批评。</p><p>今年夏天早些时候，首席执行官丹尼尔·埃克(Daniel Ek) <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-fans-and-artists-hit-back-as-spotify-ceo-claims-the-cost-of-creating-content-is-close-to-zero-3761004">声称制作“内容”的成本“接近于零”，</a>遭到了广泛的反对。 </p><figure id="attachment_3777506" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3777506" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3777506" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Daniel-Ek@2000x1270.jpg" alt="Spotify 创始人兼首席执行官 Daniel Ek" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Daniel-Ek@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Daniel-Ek@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Daniel-Ek@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Daniel-Ek@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Daniel-Ek@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Daniel-Ek@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3777506" class="wp-caption-text"> Spotify 创始人兼首席执行官 Daniel Ek（摄影：Ilya S. Savenok/Getty Images for Spotify）</figcaption></figure><p> Ek 在谈到 X/Twitter 时表示，借助现代技术，创建“内容”比以往任何时候都更容易、更实惠。 “如今，随着创建内容的成本接近于零，人们可以分享数量惊人的内容。这激发了我对长保质期与短保质期概念的好奇，”他写道。</p><p> “虽然我们看到和听到的很多东西很快就会过时，但有一些永恒的想法甚至音乐片段可以在几十年甚至几个世纪内保持相关性，”他在提问之前补充道：“我们现在创造的东西仍然会受到重视。”并讨论从今天起的数百年或数千年？”</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-fans-and-artists-hit-back-as-spotify-ceo-claims-the-cost-of-creating-content-is-close-to-zero-3761004">此番言论很快在网络社区引起反响，无数音乐爱好者和音乐人站出来批评这位首席执行官“脱离现实”</a> 。</p><p> “我本身不创造‘内容’。我创作音乐，” <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kt-tunstall">KT Tunstall</a>写道。 “廉价地制作音乐是*可能*的，但你仍然需要设备。按照我的方式制作音乐也会雇用其他人并且需要时间，所以是的。他说这种话真是太他妈的短视了。”</p><p>音乐联盟的未来也发表了类似的评论，他写道：“制作唱片实际上仍然很昂贵，特别是如果你关心公平地支付你的合作者的话”，<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/primal-scream">原始尖叫</a>贝斯手西蒙·玛丽·巴特勒写道：“滚开你脱离现实的亿万富翁。” </p><figure id="attachment_3777507" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3777507" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3777507" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify-homescreen@2000x1270.jpg" alt="2024 年 Spotify 音乐应用主页" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify-homescreen@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify-homescreen@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify-homescreen@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify-homescreen@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify-homescreen@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Spotify-homescreen@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3777507" class="wp-caption-text"> 2024 年 Spotify 音乐应用主页。图片来源：Michael M. Santiago/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p>竞争对手流媒体平台 Tidal 也在 X 上重申，它将音乐视为“艺术”而不是“内容”，而<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/deadmau5-considering-removing-music-from-spotify-after-daniel-eks-comments-fucking-vultures-3769054">Deadmau5 表示，由于这些评论，他很想从该服务中撤回自己的唱片</a>，并将其称为“秃鹰”。</p><p>在遭到强烈反对后， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotifys-daniel-ek-tidal-fac-respond-to-backlash-of-ceo-saying-content-costs-close-to-zero-to-make-3762073">埃克接着分享了另一条最新消息，为忽视音乐家所面临的困境并使用“内容”的“还原”标签而道歉</a>。</p><p> 2024 年第一季度， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-announce-profit-and-millions-more-subscribers-but-also-royalty-cuts-to-less-popular-tracks-3521362">优质订阅用户数量增长 14%，</a>达到 2.39 亿，Spotify 宣布利润超过 10 亿欧元（合 8.6 亿英镑），创历史新高。此后，还有报道称， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-removes-russian-artists-who-support-ukraine-war-3771472">它已开始从流媒体平台上删除支持乌克兰战争的俄罗斯艺术家</a>。</p><p>尽管争议首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-record-quarterly-profits-246million-premium-subscribers-despite-controversies-3777495">但 Spotify 创纪录的季度利润使优质订阅用户增至 2.46 亿</a>。</p> ;
